\begin{abstract}
The OpenAIRE Research Graph Dump provides a wide range of metadata about grant-supported research publications. Here, we present the R package openairegraph with helpers for splitting, de-compressing and parsing this data release. Our implementation aims at data science practitioners and re- searchers alike who wish to conduct their own statistical analysis using the OpenAIRE Research Graph, but are wary of handling large data. Following the the R package structure provides a standard way to ensure the computational reproducibility of our implementation. The availability of such reliable tools for statistical computing environments can greatly improve re-use of big scholarly data dumps in quantitative science studies and data-based decision-making.

\keywords{OpenAIRE  \and Big Scholarly Data \and R}
\end{abstract}
